- 'Sail above the 80% accuracy mark' refers to having an average top-1 accuracy greater than 80%.;
- 'Vast ocean of 2023' is a metaphor for the entire duration of the year 2023, indicating the period in which the models were created. ;
- 'Judged by the Top-1 accuracy metric' means that the performance evaluation criterion used is the Top-1 accuracy, which is a common measure of model performance, especially in classification tasks.
